    "description": "Muto Seiko Co., together with its subsidiaries, manufactures and sells plastic parts in Japan, Vietnam, China, Taiwan, rest of Asia, and internationally. It operates through Plastic Molding Business, Precision Press Parts Business, and Printed Circuit Board Business segments. The company offers plastic parts for digital home appliances, such as digital and video cameras; for center panel units, including car navigation systems, air conditioners, and audio equipment; and for automotive-related parts, which include ETCs. It also provides molds for injection molding and pressing. In addition, the company offers printer paper feed parts and electronic pens; and technical support services. Further, it engages in the design, inspection, and sale of printed circuit boards. Muto Seiko Co. was founded in 1956 and is headquartered in Kakamigahara, Japan."
